Male palp (
Figs 1–2
). Tibia short, as long as wide, without well developed keel. Dorsal apophysis large and distinct, distally bifid, lateral aphophysis well developed, provided with characteristic sharp outgrowth. Tegular apophysis hooked. Conductor large and folded. Embolus long, slender and tapering.

Epigyne and vulva (
Figs 5–7
). Genital plate wider than high, provided with slanting genital openings. Vulva with long coiled and looped ducts.
